The clue to the mystery - that is, mystery so far as Partner is concerned - lies in the card of his suit that you return. Since you held four hearts originally, you should not return the eight, but the three - the card that was originally your fourth best in the suit. When Declarer plays the nine your Partner will win with the Ten and now he can tell that Declarer holds only one more heart, the lone Jack. Consequently he will promptly lay down his King and drop the unguarded Jack.|
